<section xml:id="sec-appE-classical-vector-calculus-translated-into-forms" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Classical vector calculus translated into forms</title>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-gradient">
    <title>Gradient</title>

    <p>
      Classical:
      <md>\nabla f=(f_x,f_y,f_z).</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Forms:
      <md>df=f_x\,dx+f_y\,dy+f_z\,dz.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Translation:
      <md>df(\mathbf v)=\nabla f\cdot \mathbf v.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-work-form">
    <title>Work form</title>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\mathbf F=(P,Q,R),</md>
      classical line integral:
      <md>\int_C \mathbf F\cdot d\mathbf r.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Forms:
      <md>\omega_{\mathbf F}=P\,dx+Q\,dy+R\,dz.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>
        \int_C \mathbf F\cdot d\mathbf r
        =
        \int_C \omega_{\mathbf F}.
      </md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-curl">
    <title>Curl</title>

    <p>
      Classical:
      <md>
        \nabla\times\mathbf F
        =
        (R_y-Q_z,\ P_z-R_x,\ Q_x-P_y).
      </md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Forms:
      <md>
        d\omega_{\mathbf F}
        =
        (R_y-Q_z)\,dy\wedge dz
        +
        (P_z-R_x)\,dz\wedge dx
        +
        (Q_x-P_y)\,dx\wedge dy.
      </md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Translation:
      <md>
        d\omega_{\mathbf F}
        =
        \Phi_{\nabla\times\mathbf F}.
      </md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-flux-form">
    <title>Flux form</title>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\mathbf F=(P,Q,R),</md>
      classical flux:
      <md>\iint_S \mathbf F\cdot\widehat{\mathbf n}\,dS.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Forms:
      <md>
        \Phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        P\,dy\wedge dz
        +
        Q\,dz\wedge dx
        +
        R\,dx\wedge dy.
      </md>
    </p>

    <p>
      <md>
        \iint_S \mathbf F\cdot\widehat{\mathbf n}\,dS
        =
        \iint_S \Phi_{\mathbf F}.
      </md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-divergence">
    <title>Divergence</title>

    <p>
      Classical:
      <md>\nabla\cdot\mathbf F=P_x+Q_y+R_z.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Forms:
      <md>
        d\Phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        (P_x+Q_y+R_z)\,dx\wedge dy\wedge dz.
      </md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Translation:
      <md>
        d\Phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        (\nabla\cdot\mathbf F)\,dV.
      </md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-plane-circulation">
    <title>Plane circulation</title>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\mathbf F=(P,Q),</md>
      work form:
      <md>\omega=P\,dx+Q\,dy.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Scalar curl:
      <md>\operatorname{curl}_{\mathrm{plane}}\mathbf F=Q_x-P_y.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Forms:
      <md>d\omega=(Q_x-P_y)\,dx\wedge dy.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-plane-flux">
    <title>Plane flux</title>

    <p>
      For
      <md>\mathbf F=(M,N),</md>
      the outward flux form on a positively oriented boundary is
      <md>\phi_{\mathbf F}=M\,dy-N\,dx.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Then
      <md>
        \int_{\partial R}\phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        \int_{\partial R}\mathbf F\cdot\widehat{\mathbf n}\,ds.
      </md>
    </p>

    <p>
      Its exterior derivative is
      <md>
        d\phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        (M_x+N_y)\,dx\wedge dy.
      </md>
    </p>

    <p>
      So
      <md>
        d\phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        (\nabla\cdot\mathbf F)\,dA.
      </md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-vector-identities-d-squared-zero">
    <title>Vector identities from <m>d^2=0</m></title>

    <p>
      From
      <md>d(df)=0,</md>
      we get
      <md>\nabla\times(\nabla f)=\mathbf 0.</md>
    </p>

    <p>
      From
      <md>d(d\omega_{\mathbf F})=0,</md>
      we get
      <md>\nabla\cdot(\nabla\times\mathbf F)=0.</md>
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="appE-trans-common-dictionary">
    <title>Common dictionary</title>

    <table xml:id="appE-trans-tab-common-dictionary">
      <title>Classical language and forms language.</title>
      <tabular>
        <col right="minor"/>
        <col/>
        <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
          <cell>Classical language</cell>
          <cell>Forms language</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>f</m></cell>
          <cell><m>0\text{-form}</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\nabla f</m></cell>
          <cell><m>df</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\mathbf F\cdot d\mathbf r</m></cell>
          <cell><m>P\,dx+Q\,dy+R\,dz</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\nabla\times\mathbf F</m></cell>
          <cell><m>d(P\,dx+Q\,dy+R\,dz)</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\mathbf F\cdot\widehat{\mathbf n}\,dS</m></cell>
          <cell><m>P\,dy\wedge dz+Q\,dz\wedge dx+R\,dx\wedge dy</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell><m>\nabla\cdot\mathbf F</m></cell>
          <cell><m>d\Phi_{\mathbf F}</m></cell>
        </row>
      </tabular>
    </table>
  </subsection>

  <warning xml:id="appE-trans-common-warnings">
    <title>Common warnings</title>
    <p>
      The same vector field <m>\mathbf F</m> can produce two different forms:
      <md>\omega_{\mathbf F}=P\,dx+Q\,dy+R\,dz</md>
      for work and circulation.
      <md>
        \Phi_{\mathbf F}
        =
        P\,dy\wedge dz+Q\,dz\wedge dx+R\,dx\wedge dy
      </md>
      for flux.
    </p>
    <p>Do not confuse these.</p>
  </warning>
</section>
